      • actNumEdges

        private int actNumEdges
        The number of edges this node is actually supposed to actually have.

        Used to determine if graph is complete or not. (Defaults to UNDETERMINED_NUM_EDGES ('-1'))

      • attributes

        private java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> attributes
        User defined attributes of the node, defaults to empty

      • UNDETERMINED_NUM_EDGES

        public static final int UNDETERMINED_NUM_EDGES
        The default value given to actNumEdges. Value always '-1'.

      • isFull

        public boolean isFull()
        Determines if the node is full. Will never be full if actNumEdges = UNDETERMINED_NUM_EDGES

        Does not check if those edges are actually connected to other nodes. See isFullAndConnected() for that.

        Returns:
        If the node is full or not.

      • isFullAndConnected

        public boolean isFullAndConnected()
        Determines if the node is full, and edges all have nodes. Will never be full if actNumEdges = UNDETERMINED_NUM_EDGES
        Returns:
        If the node is full or not, and all edges have an end node.
